<subSubSection lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="176" pageId="22" pageNumber="175" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="22.[136,1452,1658,2081]" lastBlockId="23.[136,1452,158,509]" lastPageId="23" lastPageNumber="176" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,265,1658,1684]" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Notes:</emphasis>
— 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1851" baseAuthorityName="Naudin" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[294,550,1658,1684]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="22" pageNumber="175" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis box="[294,550,1658,1684]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Bertolonia marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
occurs in the states of 
<collectingRegion box="[832,900,1658,1684]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Bahia</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[913,1005,1658,1684]" country="Brazil" name="Alagoas" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Alagoas</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[1068,1212,1658,1684]" country="Brazil" name="Pernambuco" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Pernambuco</collectingRegion>
. This species occurs in lowland rainforests, rarely in montane rainforests with some specimens distributed in transition areas between Atlantic Forest and Caatinga (
<figureCitation box="[477,573,1730,1756]" captionStart="FIGURE 13" captionStartId="19.[136,229,1730,1752]" captionTargetBox="[346,1239,435,1693]" captionTargetId="figure-140@19.[340,1247,425,1706]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 13. Distributions of species of Bertolonia in Bahia.A.Bertolonia linearifolia. B. Bertolonia maculata. C. Bertolonia marmorata. D. Bertolonia reginatoi. E. Bertolonia riocontensis. F. Bertolonia violacea. G. Bertolonia vitoriana." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597718" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597718/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Fig. 13c</figureCitation>
), usually on forested areas near water. Collected with flowers and fruits from October to February and July. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1851" baseAuthorityName="Naudin" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[488,743,1766,1792]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="22" pageNumber="175" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis box="[488,743,1766,1792]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Bertolonia marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is recognized by the leaves with a rounded apex and flowers with small anthers (
<quantity box="[358,474,1802,1829]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.8" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.6" pageId="22" pageNumber="175" unit="mm" value="1.8" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.6">1.6–2 mm</quantity>
long) dehiscing through a triangular, introrse pore. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1851" baseAuthorityName="Naudin" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[1057,1310,1802,1828]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="22" pageNumber="175" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis box="[1057,1310,1802,1828]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Bertolonia marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Baumgratz" authorityYear="1990" box="[136,247,1839,1864]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="22" pageNumber="175" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="carmoi">
<emphasis box="[136,247,1839,1864]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">B. carmoi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<emphasis box="[304,447,1838,1864]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" box="[304,443,1838,1864]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="22" pageNumber="175" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">B. maculata</taxonomicName>
,
</emphasis>
and the limits between them is sometimes obscure (for more details, see the notes under both species). During this study we identified several specimens from different locations (
<emphasis box="[1168,1293,1874,1900]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Aona 1841</emphasis>
; 
<emphasis box="[1309,1444,1874,1900]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Bisewski 55</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[136,164,1910,1936]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">63</emphasis>
; 
<emphasis box="[179,338,1910,1936]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Ferreira 1852</emphasis>
; 
<emphasis box="[353,500,1910,1936]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Fiaschi 2760</emphasis>
; 
<emphasis box="[515,710,1910,1936]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">J.G. Jardim 4505</emphasis>
; 
<emphasis box="[725,877,1910,1936]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Thomas 3604</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[891,961,1910,1936]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">12500</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[975,1045,1910,1936]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">12505</emphasis>
, 
<emphasis box="[1059,1129,1910,1936]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">12295</emphasis>
) that might belong to this 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="22" pageNumber="175" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">B. maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
/ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1851" baseAuthorityName="Naudin" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[248,406,1947,1972]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="22" pageNumber="175" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis box="[248,406,1947,1972]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">B. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex, They all share the branches, petioles, leaf blades, hypanthium and sepals covered with sessile or short-stalked glands (less than 
<quantity box="[653,740,1982,2009]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="175" unit="mm" value="0.1">0.1 mm</quantity>
long) and long-stalked glands (
<quantity box="[1098,1192,1982,2009]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="22" pageNumber="175" unit="mm" value="3.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="1.0">1–5 mm</quantity>
long), leaf blades with similar sizes (3–14.5 × 
<quantity box="[405,548,2018,2045]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.65" metricValueMax="10.9" metricValueMin="2.4" pageId="22" pageNumber="175" unit="cm" value="6.65" valueMax="10.9" valueMin="2.4">2.4–10.9 cm</quantity>
) and anthers with an introrse pore (
<figureCitation box="[957,1055,2018,2044]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="15.[136,229,1198,1220]" captionTargetBox="[358,1229,190,1173]" captionTargetId="figure-19@15.[358,1229,190,1173]" captionTargetPageId="15" captionText="FIGURE 10. Specimens in vivo. A. Bertolonia igrapiuna. B. B. linearifolia. C. B. reginatoi. D. B. violacea. E. B. vitoriana. F. Bertolonia sp, belonging to the B. maculata/B. marmorata species complex. Photos:A, C and D by L. F. Bacci; B by F. Michelangeli; E and F by A. M. A. Amorim." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6597710" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6597710/files/figure.png" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">Fig. 10e</figureCitation>
). Moreover, these specimens share with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1851" baseAuthorityName="Naudin" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[194,352,2055,2080]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="22" pageNumber="175" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis box="[194,352,2055,2080]" italics="true" pageId="22" pageNumber="175">B. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the elliptic or widely ovate leaf blades with a rounded apex, similar anther size with an introrse, triangular pore. We are not sure about the inclusion of these specimens in the treatments for either 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" box="[1252,1388,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="23" pageNumber="176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis box="[1252,1388,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="176">B. maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1851" baseAuthorityName="Naudin" baseAuthorityYear="1848" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="23" pageNumber="176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="176">B. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
mainly because these plants have a partially tuberous, thickened stem with plagiotropic growth, that stays hidden beneath the leaf litter; the plants are invisible during the dry season, when the deciduous leaves fall. The foliar portion of the stem seems to be thicker in periods with water availability, probably making it a water reserve structure. The development of this structure seems to be related to the habitat of the specimens; they usually occur in drier places, such as deciduous seasonal forest introgressions within the Caatinga. These observations were made in the field and still require further studies, including on the anatomy of these stems, in order to decide whether these specimens belong to either 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" box="[318,453,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="23" pageNumber="176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis box="[318,453,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="176">B. maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
or 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1851" baseAuthorityName="Naudin" baseAuthorityYear="1848" box="[491,648,411,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="23" pageNumber="176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis box="[491,648,411,436]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="176">B. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, or even to one or more undescribed species. The whole 
<taxonomicName authorityName="De Candolle" authorityYear="1828" box="[1284,1419,410,436]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="23" pageNumber="176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="maculata">
<emphasis box="[1284,1419,410,436]" italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="176">B. maculata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
/ 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Naudin" authorityYear="1851" baseAuthorityName="Naudin" baseAuthorityYear="1848" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Melastomataceae" genus="Bertolonia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="23" pageNumber="176" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="marmorata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="23" pageNumber="176">B. marmorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
complex deserves a detailed, population-based study, in order to solve the problems on the limits of these species. For more details see 
<bibRefCitation author="Baumgratz, J. F. A." box="[464,669,482,509]" pageId="23" pageNumber="176" pagination="69 - 213" refId="ref18783" refString="Baumgratz, J. F. A. (1990) O genero Bertolonia Raddi (Melastomataceae): revisao taxonomica e consideracoes anatomicas. Arquivos do Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro - Serie Botanica 30: 69 - 213." type="journal article" year="1990">Baumgratz (1990)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<tableCitation box="[723,806,482,508]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="6.[136,224,623,649]" captionText="TABLE 1. Selected morphological characters scored for species in Bertolonia that occur in the state of Bahia, Brazil. “GP”= Glandulose-punctate; “GV”= Glandulose-villose." pageId="23" pageNumber="176">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
</paragraph>
